config.text: Digital Change Record
Created by Kendall County GIS

Welcome to the

Kendall County GIS

Digital Change Record!

This viewer is meant to show all significant changes made to the Kendall County maps, as well as to direct users to the relevant documents involved in a given change.


By presenting this information in a clear, interactive manner, our hope is to make these changes as accessible and transparent as possible.


To see the specific instructions for each page, click the other section titles above, or click the arrows at the sides of this panel.


Click the Help button in the lower-left at any time to display this again.
Using the Taxing Bodies Page

This page will show historic ordinance-based changes to taxing bodies within Kendall County.


What is a "taxing body"?


A taxing body is any entity that levies taxes. When you look at your property taxes, you can see that a certain amount goes to the schools, another amount to the library district, etc. Those entities are the taxing bodies your property falls within.


Navigating

At the left side of the page, you will find a list of document numbers. Clicking any of these items will zoom to the relevant area and filter the maps to show the features involved.


Above this list are filters. You can toggle the different record types on and off, and set a range for the recorded date, and the list will update accordingly.


Within the list, you can search for specific document and ordinance numbers, as well as change the sort order.


The Map

In the center of the screen is the map. This map shows any features which were annexed or deannexed by the selected document.


PINs List

The list at the right shows the PINs involved in the selected ordinance. Click on a PIN in this list to see it flash on the map.


This list can be collapsed by clicking the arrow tab on the left edge of the list.

Using the Zoning Page

This page will show historic ordinance-based changes to zoning in Kendall County, as well as the establishing and revoking of zoning permits.


Navigating

At the left side of the page, you will find a list of document numbers. Clicking any of these items will zoom to the relevant area and filter the maps to show the features involved.


Above this list are filters. You can toggle the different record types on and off, and set a range for the recorded date, and the list will update accordingly.


Within the list, you can search for specific document and ordinance numbers, as well as change the sort order.


The Maps

In the center of the screen are the Before and After maps. These show zoning features established and/or revoked by a given record.


PINs List

The list at the right shows the PINs involved in the selected ordinance. Click on a PIN in this list to see it flash on the map.


This list can be collapsed by clicking the arrow tab on the left edge of the list.

Using the Cadastre Page

This page will show historic changes to cadastral features within Kendall County.


What is a "cadastre"?


The word "cadastre" refers to the public register of real property, especially as it relates to boundaries and ownership. Besides parcels, this also concerns such features as:


  • Subdivisions
  • Condominiums
  • Right-of-Ways


The Records Panel

At the left side of the page, you will find a list of document numbers. Clicking any of these items will update the rest of the page to show features and details specific to that record.


Above this list are filters. You can toggle the different townships on and off, and set a range for the recorded date, and the list will update accordingly.


Note: Most changes occur within a single township. There are, however, cases when a change spans more than one. In such cases, the township filter may not return the desired result.


Within the list, you can search for specific document numbers, as well as change the sort order.


The Before and After Maps

To the right of the records list, you will see two maps, labelled "before" and "after". When a record is selected, these maps will zoom the the relevant area and show any features created or retired by the record.


Record Details

In the upper-right, you can view additional details about the selected record, as well as link to the original document on the County Recorder's website.


If the selected record has any attachments, they will appear here.


Legend

To the right of the "after" map, you can find a legend which explains the various polygon types displayed in the map.


PIN Details Section

If you scroll down, you will see an additional section specific to parcels that were created or retired by the selected document.


Pin Lists

On the left are the lists of PINs that were retired or created by the document. Clicking PINs in either list will update the items to the right.


Attributes / Map

On the right you can find detailed information about the selected parcel. There is also a button to switch to a map view which will highlight the selected parcel specifically.


Exporting PIN Details

In each PIN list, there is an icon in the upper-right. Click this icon to view download options. You may download the data for the listed parcels in a variety of formats for use in other programs or processes.
